Class Offset

java.lang.Object
  com.amazon.device.associates.Offset
All Implemented Interfaces:
android.os.Parcelable
public class Offset
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.os.Parcelable

An Offset is used in the ReceiptsRequest constructor to specify the starting point for retrieving the receipts. If you are making the first call to ShoppingService.getReceipts(ReceiptsRequest) or want to retrieve all receipts, pass BEGINNING. The next offset is returned in ReceiptsResponse The app can cache this object to retrieve only new receipts in the next call to ShoppingService.getReceipts(ReceiptsRequest).
